WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.711 --> 00:00:04.754
[Benya] <i>My fellow
global citizens.</i>

2
00:00:04.755 --> 00:00:10.593
<i>Today at 0942 UTC. the global community
will attempt a coordinated response</i>

3
00:00:10.594 --> 00:00:13.262
<i>to the alien aggressors
who have invaded our world.</i>

4
00:00:13.263 --> 00:00:15.307
[rap music plays]

5
00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:23.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

6
00:00:25.025 --> 00:00:26.567
[engine growls. revving]

7
00:00:26.568 --> 00:00:28.695
[rap music continues
through phone]

8
00:00:30.239 --> 00:00:31.532
[gearbox creaking]

9
00:00:36.119 --> 00:00:37.120
[Monty grunts]

10
00:00:38.080 --> 00:00:39.956
- Hey! Watch the pave. bro!
- [Monty] Fuck. Sorry. Sorry.

11
00:00:39.957 --> 00:00:41.667
- Monty!
- [sighs]

12
00:00:42.543 --> 00:00:44.753
You find it yet? The
hospital's address.

13
00:00:46.630 --> 00:00:48.090
I think it's this building here.

14
00:00:48.799 --> 00:00:50.199
[in French] <i>Septième
arrondissement.</i>

15
00:00:50.717 --> 00:00:52.009
[in English] Caspar's
got good taste.

16
00:00:52.010 --> 00:00:54.221
[chuckles] Sorry. was that
supposed to be French?

17
00:00:54.721 --> 00:00:57.431
Monty's French teacher says
his consonants are clumsy.

18
00:00:57.432 --> 00:01:00.226
My French is excellent. okay?
I just need a bit of practice.

19
00:01:00.227 --> 00:01:02.312
Oh. okay. Cool. no
problem. Repeat after me.

20
00:01:02.896 --> 00:01:05.606
[in French accent] Shia
LaBeouf. Zooey Deschanel.

21
00:01:05.607 --> 00:01:07.984
- uh. Timothée Chalamet.
- [Darwin chuckles]

22
00:01:07.985 --> 00:01:09.944
- Uh. Beyoncé? Yeah.
- Ah. Beyoncé? [laughs]

23
00:01:09.945 --> 00:01:13.489
- Can we please change the music?
- No. Pen. Give that back now.

24
00:01:13.490 --> 00:01:15.491
- [Penny] Trap. Rap.
- Pen. Stop.

25
00:01:15.492 --> 00:01:17.410
- Pen. stop.
- More rap.

26
00:01:17.411 --> 00:01:19.496
Wait. what's this?

27
00:01:20.163 --> 00:01:22.165
["Kiss from a Rose" playing]

28
00:01:24.376 --> 00:01:26.836
[Penny. Alfie. Darwin laugh]

29
00:01:26.837 --> 00:01:28.338
Is this "Kiss from a Rose"?

30
00:01:29.089 --> 00:01:30.965
- Pen. turn that off now.
- [chuckling] Are you kidding?

31
00:01:30.966 --> 00:01:32.593
- [Monty] Pen.
- Turn that up.

32
00:01:34.344 --> 00:01:37.389
Oh. shit. Slow down.
Monty. slow down. Look!

33
00:01:40.726 --> 00:01:42.019
[people chattering]

34
00:01:48.692 --> 00:01:49.942
[engine stops]

35
00:01:49.943 --> 00:01:51.278
[Monty] Fucking hell.

36
00:01:52.654 --> 00:01:55.157
- [people murmuring] - [radio
broadcaster speaks indistinctly]

37
00:01:55.741 --> 00:01:57.117
[Alfie] What they
all looking at?

38
00:01:58.535 --> 00:01:59.786
Hey. W... [stammers]

39
00:02:03.916 --> 00:02:04.917
[Jamila] Excuse me.

40
00:02:05.417 --> 00:02:07.698
- What's happening?
- [soldier] Tunnel's closed. No entry.

41
00:02:07.961 --> 00:02:10.338
- [radio chatter]
- Closed? Why?

42
00:02:10.339 --> 00:02:12.256
Last train from France
never made it here.

43
00:02:12.257 --> 00:02:13.549
Recon team went
in. never came out.

44
00:02:13.550 --> 00:02:16.135
Now the French are threatening
to close their end permanently.

45
00:02:16.136 --> 00:02:19.431
So either you and the Jag can turn around
now. or you can wait like the rest of us.

46
00:02:19.932 --> 00:02:22.976
- Wait for what?
- What. you not got a radio in that thing?

47
00:02:23.477 --> 00:02:25.758
It's been playing on loop since
she made the announcement.

48
00:02:38.951 --> 00:02:40.619
- What is it? What's happening?
- Shh.

49
00:02:44.706 --> 00:02:47.250
[Benya] <i>...outnumbered.
outflanked. outgunned.</i>

50
00:02:47.251 --> 00:02:49.502
<i>I cannot guarantee
that we will succeed.</i>

51
00:02:49.503 --> 00:02:52.964
<i>but what I can say is we'll try
to hit them back where it hurts.</i>

52
00:02:52.965 --> 00:02:54.715
- "Hit them back"? Wh... -
<i>Let them feel a fraction...</i>

53
00:02:54.716 --> 00:02:57.468
- It's an... It's an attack. It's gotta be.
- Monty?

54
00:02:57.469 --> 00:02:59.095
- It's fine. It's fine.
- <i>"Never let them see you</i>

55
00:02:59.096 --> 00:03:00.471
<i>with your head bowed."</i>

56
00:03:00.472 --> 00:03:03.641
<i>So I ask you now to look up.</i>

57
00:03:03.642 --> 00:03:05.811
<i>Look up. Let us no...</i>

58
00:03:06.603 --> 00:03:08.479
The hell are you doing?
Something's happening.

59
00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:10.231
Yeah. we're taking
that tunnel to France.

60
00:03:10.232 --> 00:03:12.733
- We are?
- Are you completely nuts?

61
00:03:12.734 --> 00:03:14.653
Turn around and drive.

62
00:03:16.780 --> 00:03:18.031
[engine starts]

63
00:03:30.878 --> 00:03:32.128
So let me get this straight.

64
00:03:32.129 --> 00:03:34.797
you're still keen to go in.
despite the military warnings?

65
00:03:34.798 --> 00:03:37.551
- Are we going to get arrested?
- No. we're not.

66
00:03:38.719 --> 00:03:40.554
- Are we?
- There's the tunnel.

67
00:03:44.057 --> 00:03:45.266
Shit.

68
00:03:45.267 --> 00:03:47.643
No good. We'll never scale that
fence without somebody seeing.

69
00:03:47.644 --> 00:03:49.124
[Darwin] How are
we gonna get in then?

70
00:03:51.148 --> 00:03:53.358
- There! Monty. pull up there now.
- [Monty] Yeah.

71
00:04:03.619 --> 00:04:04.702
[engine stops]

72
00:04:04.703 --> 00:04:07.503
- [Alfie] Think it leads to the tunnel?
- [Jamila] One way to find out.

73
00:04:09.249 --> 00:04:10.333
- [Jamila sighs]
- Hey. wait.

74
00:04:10.334 --> 00:04:12.044
[Alfie] I'll get the
crowbar from the boot.

75
00:04:15.172 --> 00:04:17.756
This is all. I mean. if
soldiers went down...

76
00:04:17.757 --> 00:04:19.593
You know. it's...

77
00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:23.513
[sighs. scoffs]

78
00:04:23.514 --> 00:04:25.849
Okay. look. It's not
about me. okay? I just...

79
00:04:29.186 --> 00:04:30.646
I can't let nothing
happen to her.

80
00:04:33.273 --> 00:04:34.274
It's all good.

81
00:04:35.025 --> 00:04:37.027
You've gotten us this far.

82
00:04:37.861 --> 00:04:39.029
so thank you.

83
00:04:40.113 --> 00:04:42.783
Does this mean we're not
going to save Mum and Dad?

84
00:04:47.204 --> 00:04:48.564
[Darwin] Would
you like me to help?

85
00:04:55.671 --> 00:04:58.590
Course we're going to
save Mum and Dad. okay?

86
00:04:59.466 --> 00:05:01.301
Look. it just means
when we get there.

87
00:05:02.010 --> 00:05:04.554
I need you to listen to
me and do whatever I say.

88
00:05:04.555 --> 00:05:08.975
and not be your usual
annoying. whining. clawing self.

89
00:05:08.976 --> 00:05:10.059
Okay? Can you do that?

90
00:05:10.060 --> 00:05:12.478
Yes. as long as you're not
your usual manky. numpty...

91
00:05:12.479 --> 00:05:13.729
- Yeah.
- Knobhead self...

92
00:05:13.730 --> 00:05:15.649
- [Monty] Yeah. Sod off. please.
- [door closes]

93
00:05:17.067 --> 00:05:18.068
[Monty sighs]

94
00:05:18.902 --> 00:05:20.237
What? You think
we wasn't coming?

95
00:05:20.737 --> 00:05:22.417
- Let's go then.
- [Darwin. Alfie grunting]

96
00:05:22.906 --> 00:05:24.950
[Darwin] Push harder. you dick.

97
00:05:44.136 --> 00:05:45.762
[soldiers chattering]

98
00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:47.680
[Alfie] Shit. Soldiers.

99
00:05:47.681 --> 00:05:50.017
[Jamila] Quick.
Before they see us. Go.

100
00:06:16.627 --> 00:06:17.627
[Alfie] Here we are.

101
00:06:24.009 --> 00:06:27.304
Looks like the. uh.
point of no return. Eh?

102
00:06:27.930 --> 00:06:29.598
Don't worry. I thought ahead.

103
00:06:30.557 --> 00:06:31.974
[Monty] Pen. what's that?

104
00:06:31.975 --> 00:06:34.310
My report from our class
trip to the Channel Tunnel.

105
00:06:34.311 --> 00:06:36.021
I drew a map and
everything. See?

106
00:06:40.609 --> 00:06:41.860
[Alfie] I brought help too.

107
00:06:43.737 --> 00:06:46.782
Alien repellant.
Homemade flamethrower.

108
00:06:47.491 --> 00:06:48.908
Bond did it in <i>Live and Let Die</i>.

109
00:06:48.909 --> 00:06:52.578
Yeah. but. Alf. that'll just blow
your hands off. you know. in real life.

110
00:06:52.579 --> 00:06:53.747
[explosion]

111
00:06:55.040 --> 00:06:57.167
[rumbling. explosion]

112
00:06:58.877 --> 00:07:00.127
What the hell just happened?

113
00:07:00.128 --> 00:07:01.213
Are they attacking us?

114
00:07:01.922 --> 00:07:03.422
[Darwin] Or are
we attacking them?

115
00:07:03.423 --> 00:07:04.423
Power's still on.

116
00:07:05.050 --> 00:07:06.176
That's good. Let's go!

117
00:07:08.804 --> 00:07:11.514
I'm sorry. Not to be the
only one living in real life

118
00:07:11.515 --> 00:07:14.434
right now. but something absolutely
major just happened back there.

119
00:07:15.102 --> 00:07:17.728
So. new plan. we head
back just to see. you know...

120
00:07:17.729 --> 00:07:19.314
No! We stay put.

121
00:07:19.898 --> 00:07:22.108
If we go back out. they
could spot us and stop us.

122
00:07:22.109 --> 00:07:25.112
- Yeah. but we don't know what's out there.
- You're right. We don't.

123
00:07:25.654 --> 00:07:28.532
But we do know this tunnel is
the only way to get to Caspar.

124
00:07:29.658 --> 00:07:33.161
This says that the service entrance
joins up with the train tunnel up ahead.

125
00:07:38.041 --> 00:07:41.545
Look. it's fine to feel scared.

126
00:07:42.713 --> 00:07:44.256
It would be mental not to.

127
00:07:44.840 --> 00:07:47.426
But it's been four months
since those things showed up.

128
00:07:48.010 --> 00:07:50.721
And I'm so tired of this shit!

129
00:07:54.474 --> 00:07:59.313
My mum told me once in
critical surgery or whatever.

130
00:08:00.397 --> 00:08:01.607
there's. like. this moment

131
00:08:02.399 --> 00:08:04.735
when the body on the
table makes a choice.

132
00:08:05.569 --> 00:08:06.986
To fight

133
00:08:06.987 --> 00:08:09.448
or to let go. and you
can see it happen.

134
00:08:10.699 --> 00:08:13.327
Our friend is waiting for us.

135
00:08:14.328 --> 00:08:17.623
If we can find him. maybe
our species at least has a shot.

136
00:08:18.498 --> 00:08:20.249
So this is it. the moment.

137
00:08:20.250 --> 00:08:23.253
Do we fight or let go?

138
00:08:28.884 --> 00:08:30.302
For Caspar.

139
00:08:34.972 --> 00:08:36.015
[Alfie] For Casp.

140
00:08:37.351 --> 00:08:38.559
Caspar.

141
00:08:44.232 --> 00:08:45.943
Yeah. Right. We're
in too then. I guess.

142
00:10:29.338 --> 00:10:31.214
[radio broadcaster. in French]
<i>It's a truly momentous victory.</i>

143
00:10:31.215 --> 00:10:32.757
<i>For those now joining us.</i>

144
00:10:32.758 --> 00:10:36.552
<i>seven alien ships have been successfully
shot down by the World Defense Coalition.</i>

145
00:10:36.553 --> 00:10:40.139
<i>As of yet. there has been no
response from the alien invaders.</i>

146
00:10:40.140 --> 00:10:42.266
<i>nor any retaliation
from the mothership.</i>

147
00:10:42.267 --> 00:10:45.645
<i>But sources indicate that
coalition forces are optimistic</i>

148
00:10:45.646 --> 00:10:47.897
- <i>we may have dealt a critical blow.</i>
- [people applaud]

149
00:10:47.898 --> 00:10:53.695
<i>WDC President Benya Mabote has reportedly
ordered military units to the crash sites...</i>

150
00:10:55.405 --> 00:10:58.242
[reciting "Hail Mary"]

151
00:11:23.183 --> 00:11:25.310
SECURE WARD

152
00:11:34.278 --> 00:11:35.358
[neurologist speaks French]

153
00:11:57.634 --> 00:11:59.261
[beeping]

154
00:12:20.949 --> 00:12:23.410
[beeping]

155
00:12:31.460 --> 00:12:32.793
[sighs]

156
00:12:32.794 --> 00:12:35.422
You're missing
the big day. Caspar.

157
00:12:36.757 --> 00:12:39.009
Why don't you wake up
and join the fun. hmm?

158
00:12:40.511 --> 00:12:42.231
[coworker] Who's to
say he's not having fun?

159
00:12:46.141 --> 00:12:48.309
We know so little
about this one.

160
00:12:48.310 --> 00:12:50.270
Seems a shame
to assume anything.

161
00:12:50.521 --> 00:12:51.729
From his brain
activity. Gabriel.

162
00:12:51.730 --> 00:12:54.650
we can assume he's been experiencing
on average seven seizures every hour.

163
00:12:55.943 --> 00:12:57.694
Not exactly a party.

164
00:12:59.196 --> 00:13:00.655
[sighs]

165
00:13:00.656 --> 00:13:01.698
Fair enough.

166
00:13:06.828 --> 00:13:10.457
So much research on these kids
and their connection to our visitors.

167
00:13:11.583 --> 00:13:13.752
Hoping to find a key.

168
00:13:16.171 --> 00:13:18.298
Maybe after today.
we won't need one.

169
00:13:18.882 --> 00:13:21.717
[inhales sharply] Speaking of. a
few of us were going to open a bottle

170
00:13:21.718 --> 00:13:23.638
later this evening. A
little victory celebration.

171
00:13:24.263 --> 00:13:25.722
Care to join?

172
00:13:26.557 --> 00:13:27.933
Victory.

173
00:13:28.976 --> 00:13:31.477
The most important skill a
neurologist can learn Esmee.

174
00:13:31.478 --> 00:13:33.188
is knowing when
to turn their brain off.

175
00:13:36.567 --> 00:13:39.778
Especially when a
patient is beyond saving.

176
00:13:48.328 --> 00:13:50.873
[Esmee] Please wake up. Caspar.

177
00:13:54.877 --> 00:13:57.879
[Penny. in English] In school. we
spent a whole week studying bridges.

178
00:13:57.880 --> 00:13:59.922
but tunnels are
much more interesting.

179
00:13:59.923 --> 00:14:02.967
because tunnels are about
length. and tunnels are about depth.

180
00:14:02.968 --> 00:14:04.887
and tunnels are about pressure.

181
00:14:05.929 --> 00:14:09.599
Look. See that thing up there?
It's one of the piston relief ducts.

182
00:14:09.600 --> 00:14:11.726
It runs all the way through
the other train tunnel.

183
00:14:11.727 --> 00:14:14.353
Miss Malkin said if we didn't have
one of those. the pressure in here

184
00:14:14.354 --> 00:14:17.982
- would pop skulls like champagne corks.
- [Monty] Jesus Christ. Pen. That's enough.

185
00:14:17.983 --> 00:14:19.775
[Penny] They're just
entertaining facts.

186
00:14:19.776 --> 00:14:21.777
Yeah? Well. you've been
entertaining us for an hour.

187
00:14:21.778 --> 00:14:23.322
Pipe down now. yeah?

188
00:14:24.364 --> 00:14:25.699
Anyone else feel that?

189
00:14:26.658 --> 00:14:28.117
- The cold?
- I know.

190
00:14:28.118 --> 00:14:30.244
It's like. um. we're on ice
or something. like. um...

191
00:14:30.245 --> 00:14:31.746
Monty's dating life.

192
00:14:31.747 --> 00:14:33.080
That's absolute tosh. mate.

193
00:14:33.081 --> 00:14:35.750
It's true. Monty. You haven't
had a girlfriend since Brexit.

194
00:14:35.751 --> 00:14:36.834
- Penny!
- [Alfie laughs]

195
00:14:36.835 --> 00:14:39.170
- It's just a fact.
- Nobody needs to know.

196
00:14:39.171 --> 00:14:40.880
Just like nobody needs
to know about pressure

197
00:14:40.881 --> 00:14:42.965
and wiring and the other shit
you've been going on about.

198
00:14:42.966 --> 00:14:44.425
Hey. you promised
to do what I say.

199
00:14:44.426 --> 00:14:47.011
Well. now I say put a
fucking sock in it. yeah?

200
00:14:47.012 --> 00:14:48.096
Great.

201
00:14:48.805 --> 00:14:51.349
Who needs a dating life when I've
got your mom on call 24/7. mate?

202
00:14:51.350 --> 00:14:52.601
[Alfie] Shut up.

203
00:14:57.272 --> 00:14:59.190
Christ. baby
sisters are the worst.

204
00:14:59.191 --> 00:15:01.192
I'm a baby sister.

205
00:15:01.193 --> 00:15:03.403
And you were a
prick to her just now.

206
00:15:05.614 --> 00:15:07.783
She's probably nervous. I mean.

207
00:15:08.408 --> 00:15:10.285
- who wouldn't be?
- You're kidding.

208
00:15:10.786 --> 00:15:13.120
Strolling down a dark.
abandoned train tunnel

209
00:15:13.121 --> 00:15:15.361
with a thousand trillion liters
of water above our heads.

210
00:15:16.250 --> 00:15:17.375
Every kid's dream. innit?

211
00:15:17.376 --> 00:15:19.670
Yeah. A real quest for the ages.

212
00:15:20.671 --> 00:15:22.381
Oh. uh. Alfie's mom a good snog?

213
00:15:22.965 --> 00:15:25.591
Yeah. no. She's
definitely in the top ten.

214
00:15:25.592 --> 00:15:28.095
- Just under Judi Dench. so...
- [Jamila chuckles]

215
00:15:29.763 --> 00:15:31.348
So. when did you figure it out?

216
00:15:32.015 --> 00:15:33.183
About Caspar?

217
00:15:33.684 --> 00:15:34.685
Figure what?

218
00:15:35.352 --> 00:15:37.396
That he was. I
don't know. special.

219
00:15:38.605 --> 00:15:41.024
I didn't at first.

220
00:15:42.317 --> 00:15:43.318
Looking back.

221
00:15:44.027 --> 00:15:45.028
yeah.

222
00:15:45.737 --> 00:15:47.364
There was always
something about him.

223
00:15:48.198 --> 00:15:53.828
Like he was tuned into some wavelength
of some song the rest of us couldn't hear.

224
00:15:53.829 --> 00:15:55.830
[chuckles] Like his
ancient Walkman.

225
00:15:55.831 --> 00:15:57.665
[chuckles] Old stuff.

226
00:15:57.666 --> 00:16:00.209
God. I used to needle him
all the time. now that I think.

227
00:16:00.210 --> 00:16:02.503
But the truth is. I actually
thought it was pretty cool.

228
00:16:02.504 --> 00:16:03.839
Bullshit. [scoffs]

229
00:16:04.506 --> 00:16:06.258
You didn't needle
him. you hated him.

230
00:16:07.801 --> 00:16:10.511
Come on. It's not
like it's a secret.

231
00:16:10.512 --> 00:16:12.306
You were shit to him.

232
00:16:15.726 --> 00:16:18.270
Don't get me wrong.
I'm glad you're here.

233
00:16:19.563 --> 00:16:22.691
I guess I just don't
know why you're here.

234
00:16:25.485 --> 00:16:28.070
Like you said. gotta
take our world back. right?

235
00:16:28.071 --> 00:16:29.280
Simple as that.

236
00:16:29.281 --> 00:16:30.574
"Simple as that"?

237
00:16:32.367 --> 00:16:34.203
Sure. I mean. why
else would I be here?

238
00:16:35.913 --> 00:16:37.079
[Alfie] Holy shit!

239
00:16:37.080 --> 00:16:39.208
[Darwin groans] Oh. God.

240
00:16:41.376 --> 00:16:42.794
[Darwin retches. coughs]

241
00:16:44.546 --> 00:16:46.507
[coughs. retches]

242
00:16:47.257 --> 00:16:48.300
The recon team.

243
00:16:50.010 --> 00:16:51.345
Aliens did this. They're here.

244
00:16:55.432 --> 00:16:56.432
Oi. you all right?

245
00:16:56.433 --> 00:16:58.267
- Eh. back off!
- Bro. I'm just trying to help.

246
00:16:58.268 --> 00:17:00.394
Well. he doesn't want it.
does he? Not from you.

247
00:17:00.395 --> 00:17:02.522
[Darwin] Not from either of
you. I'm not a bloody invalid.

248
00:17:02.523 --> 00:17:05.192
I just wasn't
expecting to see that.

249
00:17:06.984 --> 00:17:08.569
Wait. wait. wait. Where's Penny?

250
00:17:09.863 --> 00:17:10.864
Shit. Where'd she go?

251
00:17:11.615 --> 00:17:13.741
- Penny?
- She was right behind us. wasn't she?

252
00:17:13.742 --> 00:17:15.535
[Darwin] M-Maybe she passed us.

253
00:17:15.536 --> 00:17:16.662
[aliens scuttling]

254
00:17:17.162 --> 00:17:18.955
- [growling] - Pen. get
back here right now.

255
00:17:21.834 --> 00:17:23.041
Pen?

256
00:17:23.042 --> 00:17:24.126
[scuttling continues]

257
00:17:24.127 --> 00:17:25.878
[grunt. rumbling]

258
00:17:28.006 --> 00:17:29.925
[Jamila] Oh. my God.

259
00:17:31.593 --> 00:17:32.677
- [Monty] Run!
- Go!

260
00:17:32.678 --> 00:17:34.387
- [roaring]
- [Monty shouts]

261
00:17:34.388 --> 00:17:35.638
- [Jamila] Monty.
- [Monty] Fuck.

262
00:17:35.639 --> 00:17:39.308
- Shit. I'm stuck! I'm stuck!
- [Jamila] Monty. get up. Monty!

263
00:17:39.309 --> 00:17:40.811
Pull! Pull!

264
00:17:41.478 --> 00:17:42.770
[Alfie] Where's my lighter?

265
00:17:42.771 --> 00:17:44.691
- Fuck. I can't find my lighter.
- [Jamila] Guys.

266
00:17:45.190 --> 00:17:46.650
- Oh. shit!
- [both panting]

267
00:17:49.069 --> 00:17:50.654
[roars]

268
00:17:51.864 --> 00:17:53.740
[beeping]

269
00:17:58.996 --> 00:18:00.873
Fuck. [breathing heavily]

270
00:18:05.210 --> 00:18:06.420
Fuck.

271
00:18:07.713 --> 00:18:09.214
What happened to that thing?

272
00:18:09.756 --> 00:18:11.967
It looked. I don't know. sick.

273
00:18:12.759 --> 00:18:15.261
[Darwin] It's really cold.
I can feel it from here.

274
00:18:15.262 --> 00:18:16.512
I think it stopped breathing.

275
00:18:16.513 --> 00:18:18.639
[Alfie] Did it even
breathe? Or have lungs or...

276
00:18:18.640 --> 00:18:20.433
Whatever. who gives a shit?

277
00:18:20.434 --> 00:18:23.896
Penny's missing. and you lot are going
on about this-this fucking thing's anatomy.

278
00:18:24.396 --> 00:18:27.064
The only breathing I care
about right now. yeah. is Penny's.

279
00:18:27.065 --> 00:18:29.859
[Penny] You always said my
breath smells like dead rats.

280
00:18:29.860 --> 00:18:31.278
[Monty] Pen. Oh. my God.

281
00:18:31.987 --> 00:18:34.947
Come on. Don't ever
run away like that. yeah?

282
00:18:34.948 --> 00:18:36.699
I wasn't running.
I was exploring.

283
00:18:36.700 --> 00:18:40.120
And if you like that lumpy thing.
you're going to love what I found.

284
00:18:43.624 --> 00:18:44.704
[patient. in Malay] Broken.

285
00:18:57.721 --> 00:18:59.014
Home.

286
00:19:00.682 --> 00:19:01.767
Mm-hmm.

287
00:19:15.989 --> 00:19:18.450
Soon.

288
00:19:22.037 --> 00:19:23.037
[Esmee stammers]

289
00:19:23.330 --> 00:19:25.498
[Gabriel. in French]
They're finished. it's over!

290
00:19:25.499 --> 00:19:27.501
Just the person who
needs to see this.

291
00:19:28.168 --> 00:19:29.461
[in Malay] A moment. Prisha.

292
00:19:31.004 --> 00:19:33.214
[Gabriel. in French] I was
on a walk to clear my head.

293
00:19:33.215 --> 00:19:37.010
and a few blocks
from here. saw this.

294
00:19:39.096 --> 00:19:40.681
It's happening all over.

295
00:19:42.057 --> 00:19:43.350
They're dying. Esmee.

296
00:19:44.309 --> 00:19:45.309
We did it.

297
00:19:46.228 --> 00:19:47.396
We did it.

298
00:19:53.944 --> 00:19:56.487
- [Alfie. in English] What's that?
- [Penny] A crossway. They're on the map.

299
00:19:56.488 --> 00:19:58.865
- We walked right by it.
- [Jamila] Where does it lead?

300
00:19:58.866 --> 00:20:01.076
[Penny] Another tunnel
for workers. I think.

301
00:20:01.660 --> 00:20:05.163
There's no tracks to trip up
on. which means we go faster.

302
00:20:06.039 --> 00:20:07.124
[Jamila] Lead the way.

303
00:20:13.922 --> 00:20:15.424
See? What did I tell you?

304
00:20:22.389 --> 00:20:23.890
Penny. be careful. you nutter.

305
00:20:23.891 --> 00:20:25.641
It's okay. I was
scared too at first.

306
00:20:25.642 --> 00:20:29.605
But this lot's dead as...
[chuckles] ...dodos. Ice-cold too.

307
00:20:35.235 --> 00:20:38.070
[Jamila] That's why the
temperature's so low. All of these things.

308
00:20:38.071 --> 00:20:41.324
[Darwin] Think it was the attack they were
talking about on radio that killed them?

309
00:20:41.325 --> 00:20:44.452
[Penny] Maybe. Maybe they'll
just curl up and leave us alone.

310
00:20:44.453 --> 00:20:45.786
Wouldn't that be terrific?

311
00:20:45.787 --> 00:20:48.247
[Monty] Please. They're not all
gonna catch the flu and die. Pen.

312
00:20:48.248 --> 00:20:49.582
[Alfie] You don't know that.

313
00:20:49.583 --> 00:20:51.292
[Monty] You looked up
at the sky recently. mate?

314
00:20:51.293 --> 00:20:53.586
You didn't see anything highly
evolved up there. did you?

315
00:20:53.587 --> 00:20:56.923
[Alfie] Haven't seen nothing highly
evolved down here. for sure. [chuckles]

316
00:20:56.924 --> 00:20:59.050
[Darwin] Would you two
just back off each other?

317
00:20:59.051 --> 00:21:00.928
Jamila. w-what's going on?

318
00:21:02.763 --> 00:21:04.348
[whirring]

319
00:21:09.311 --> 00:21:10.811
[humming]

320
00:21:10.812 --> 00:21:12.063
[Alfie] What is it?

321
00:21:12.064 --> 00:21:13.148
[Jamila] Don't know.

322
00:21:24.326 --> 00:21:25.953
Let me try something.

323
00:21:46.098 --> 00:21:48.392
[resonating hum]

324
00:22:01.822 --> 00:22:03.866
[bottles hum]

325
00:22:12.291 --> 00:22:15.919
[Alfie] What's that noise? Sounds like
my mum's wind chimes or something.

326
00:22:17.004 --> 00:22:18.797
[whirring. humming stop]

327
00:22:21.717 --> 00:22:23.885
Show's over. I guess.

328
00:22:23.886 --> 00:22:25.554
That wasn't a show.

329
00:22:26.722 --> 00:22:28.307
It was a transmission.

330
00:22:29.433 --> 00:22:32.101
A message from them.

331
00:22:32.102 --> 00:22:33.228
[Monty] To who?

332
00:22:33.812 --> 00:22:35.230
And what did it say?

333
00:22:37.482 --> 00:22:40.026
- Come on. [breathes
deeply] - [bottle closes]

334
00:22:40.027 --> 00:22:41.945
- Let's go.
- [Monty] Let's go.

335
00:22:49.828 --> 00:22:51.580
[alien scuttling]

336
00:23:09.264 --> 00:23:11.016
[Alfie] What the
hell happened here?

337
00:23:11.600 --> 00:23:12.851
[Darwin] Is that security?

338
00:23:14.102 --> 00:23:16.021
[Jamila] Looks like
some kind of last stand.

339
00:23:17.189 --> 00:23:18.857
[Monty] Didn't
stand long. did they?

340
00:23:22.069 --> 00:23:24.571
[Alfie] This is some
straight-up Godzilla shit.

341
00:23:25.155 --> 00:23:27.698
[Darwin] They. uh. must have
been protecting something or...

342
00:23:27.699 --> 00:23:29.409
[Alfie] What? More tunnels?

343
00:23:30.911 --> 00:23:31.912
[Jamila] This.

344
00:23:33.914 --> 00:23:34.914
[Monty] Christ.

345
00:23:34.915 --> 00:23:36.915
[Jamila] They couldn't
get the gate closed in time.

346
00:23:37.459 --> 00:23:38.876
[Alfie] The aliens
slaughtered them.

347
00:23:38.877 --> 00:23:40.838
[breathing heavily]

348
00:23:41.421 --> 00:23:42.964
Penny?

349
00:23:42.965 --> 00:23:45.633
Pen. hey. hey. Hey. hey. Look at
me. Look at me. It's all right. okay?

350
00:23:45.634 --> 00:23:47.385
It's just another panic
attack. You all right?

351
00:23:47.386 --> 00:23:49.720
- We're fine. You're fine. Penny. Fine.
- I feel it. I feel it.

352
00:23:49.721 --> 00:23:51.013
- [Monty] You feel what?
- I feel it.

353
00:23:51.014 --> 00:23:53.475
- [Penny breathing
heavily] - [rumbling]

354
00:23:55.727 --> 00:23:57.087
- [panting] I feel it.
- Feel what?

355
00:24:04.570 --> 00:24:07.781
[worker. in French] Doctor... Doctor
please. I can't understand you...

356
00:24:08.448 --> 00:24:10.032
- The line is breaking up...
- [doctor. indistinct]

357
00:24:10.033 --> 00:24:11.868
- can you say that again?
- [radio static]

358
00:24:11.869 --> 00:24:14.371
It's Saint-Louis Hospital.
Something's wrong.

359
00:24:15.205 --> 00:24:16.289
Hello. this is Dr. Gagneux.

360
00:24:16.290 --> 00:24:18.792
<i>They all appear to be
victims of some kind of attack.</i>

361
00:24:19.751 --> 00:24:21.085
- <i>We're overwhelmed...</i>
- [speaks French]

362
00:24:21.086 --> 00:24:23.546
<i>we need someone to take...</i>

363
00:24:23.547 --> 00:24:26.632
- <i>We're overwhelmed. we need someone...</i>
- [in French] Doctor. are you there?

364
00:24:26.633 --> 00:24:28.009
[vehicle skidding. crashing]

365
00:24:28.010 --> 00:24:30.637
- [glass shattering]
- [people clamoring]

366
00:24:31.138 --> 00:24:33.222
EMERGENCY

367
00:24:33.223 --> 00:24:34.933
[clamoring continues]

368
00:24:40.105 --> 00:24:41.315
[siren wailing]

369
00:24:45.903 --> 00:24:49.906
- [driver groans. pants] -
Gently. gently. Breathe.

370
00:24:49.907 --> 00:24:51.449
What did this to you?

371
00:24:51.450 --> 00:24:54.119
Forget me. Get
everyone... to safety...

372
00:24:54.494 --> 00:24:57.163
- I need help over here!
- [driver groans]

373
00:24:57.164 --> 00:24:58.706
[speaks French]

374
00:24:58.707 --> 00:25:00.333
[driver strains]

375
00:25:00.334 --> 00:25:03.419
They're coming...

376
00:25:03.420 --> 00:25:05.214
and they're worse...

377
00:25:05.714 --> 00:25:07.508
[driver murmuring. groaning]

378
00:25:17.226 --> 00:25:19.645
- [person screams]
- [gunfire]

379
00:25:21.772 --> 00:25:24.816
[alien growling]

380
00:25:25.859 --> 00:25:27.402
[roaring]

381
00:25:28.362 --> 00:25:29.737
[in English] Go. go.
go. now! Go now!

382
00:25:29.738 --> 00:25:31.949
- Fuck. Move him!
- [Alfie] Shit. What do we do?

383
00:25:32.741 --> 00:25:35.285
[Monty] Darwin. Darwin.
go! Penny. go with me.

384
00:25:36.620 --> 00:25:38.413
- [Jamila] Push.
- [Alfie strains]

385
00:25:41.333 --> 00:25:42.918
[Darwin] We have
got to get out of here.

386
00:25:43.669 --> 00:25:44.669
[Monty] Hey. Penny.

387
00:25:44.670 --> 00:25:46.588
Penny. Penny. look at me.

388
00:25:47.172 --> 00:25:50.050
- Hey. Close your eyes. okay?
- [panting]

389
00:25:50.676 --> 00:25:52.385
We're going to walk
the maze together. yeah?

390
00:25:52.386 --> 00:25:55.680
Can you see it. the maze? Great.
okay. You're walking forward.

391
00:25:55.681 --> 00:25:58.766
Tall hedges on either side
protecting you. But there's a fork.

392
00:25:58.767 --> 00:26:00.101
You know where to
go. yeah? You turn...

393
00:26:00.102 --> 00:26:01.853
- Left.
- There you go. You turn left.

394
00:26:01.854 --> 00:26:02.979
Now. you're walking forward.

395
00:26:02.980 --> 00:26:05.273
<i>And then there's a
corner. Then you turn...</i>

396
00:26:05.274 --> 00:26:07.233
- [Penny] <i>Right.</i>
- [Monty] <i>Exactly. Right. yes.</i>

397
00:26:07.234 --> 00:26:10.070
- [alarm blaring] - [children
chanting] Wajo. Wajo. Wajo...

398
00:26:12.865 --> 00:26:15.116
[Esmee. in French] Everyone. listen to
me... Take the children with you and go!

399
00:26:15.117 --> 00:26:18.328
Gather all the essential
research. everything you can.

400
00:26:19.705 --> 00:26:21.081
Quickly!

401
00:26:23.584 --> 00:26:25.252
Esmee. what's going on?

402
00:26:25.586 --> 00:26:27.670
They're not dead. Gabriel.

403
00:26:27.671 --> 00:26:30.464
They're coming back.

404
00:26:30.465 --> 00:26:32.676
And they're worse.

405
00:26:36.138 --> 00:26:38.347
Get everything you can and go!

406
00:26:38.348 --> 00:26:40.058
This is not a test.

407
00:26:40.642 --> 00:26:42.144
[chanting continues]

408
00:26:43.020 --> 00:26:44.646
[Gabriel] Sarah. grab my files.

409
00:26:45.898 --> 00:26:46.898
Esmee...

410
00:26:47.107 --> 00:26:49.066
- In his condition. we can't possibly...
- [Esmee] I know.

411
00:26:49.067 --> 00:26:52.821
- [Gabriel] We'd do more harm than good.
- I said I know. Go help the others.

412
00:26:54.656 --> 00:26:55.782
And Gabriel?

413
00:26:56.283 --> 00:26:58.911
Tell the guards out there to
protect this boy at all costs.

414
00:27:04.791 --> 00:27:06.210
[machines beeping]

415
00:27:07.669 --> 00:27:09.713
You're a survivor. Caspar.

416
00:27:11.423 --> 00:27:13.550
Survive.

417
00:27:17.179 --> 00:27:19.847
- [Penny. in English] <i>I'm scared.</i>
- [Monty] <i>No. you're not. We've been here.</i>

418
00:27:19.848 --> 00:27:22.099
- Where do you turn?
- [breathing heavily] Left. Then right.

419
00:27:22.100 --> 00:27:23.184
Then right again.

420
00:27:23.185 --> 00:27:26.396
Yes. yes. yes. Now you're at
the center of the garden with me.

421
00:27:27.022 --> 00:27:29.273
- You made it.
[chuckles] - [alien rustling]

422
00:27:29.274 --> 00:27:30.901
- Yeah?
- [alien rumbling]

423
00:27:32.110 --> 00:27:33.737
[Jamila] Get back. guys! Now!

424
00:27:34.988 --> 00:27:36.949
[bellowing]

425
00:27:41.036 --> 00:27:42.412
[crashing]

426
00:27:43.747 --> 00:27:46.250
[Alfie] What the hell
are those? They're huge!

427
00:27:46.959 --> 00:27:49.253
[Jamila] Oh. God. What are they?

428
00:27:51.588 --> 00:27:54.341
- Alf? What are you doing? Alf!
- [Alfie] Fucking...

429
00:27:55.676 --> 00:27:57.052
[shouting]

430
00:28:01.390 --> 00:28:02.432
[Alfie] Yes!

431
00:28:03.642 --> 00:28:06.937
It's not working.
The fire's not working!

432
00:28:07.604 --> 00:28:08.981
Come on!

433
00:28:09.565 --> 00:28:10.565
[Monty] Go. Jump.

434
00:28:12.651 --> 00:28:14.610
- [Jamila] We have to shut the door.
- [Alfie] Here.

435
00:28:14.611 --> 00:28:16.113
- [Monty] Come on. Go.
- [door creaks]

436
00:28:17.072 --> 00:28:18.781
[Jamila] Come on.
guys! Guys. turn it.

437
00:28:18.782 --> 00:28:21.075
- [bellowing] - Guys.
the gate's giving way.

438
00:28:21.076 --> 00:28:22.910
- Hurry. Please!
- [Darwin] That's it. more to me.

439
00:28:22.911 --> 00:28:24.621
[growling]

440
00:28:25.372 --> 00:28:27.540
- [Monty] It can't go any faster!
- [Alfie] Come on! Quicker!

441
00:28:27.541 --> 00:28:30.127
[Jamila] Guys. guys. Guys.
quickly! Quickly. Darwin! Close it!

442
00:28:33.338 --> 00:28:34.672
[stomping]

443
00:28:34.673 --> 00:28:36.257
[all panting]

444
00:28:36.258 --> 00:28:37.885
[aliens bellowing]

445
00:28:41.054 --> 00:28:42.764
[metal creaking]

446
00:28:46.185 --> 00:28:48.896
- We can't stay here. Come on.
- [aliens bellowing]

447
00:28:50.564 --> 00:28:52.107
Go. go. go. go. Penny. go.

448
00:29:02.451 --> 00:29:04.661
[alien roars]

449
00:29:11.210 --> 00:29:13.462
[water dripping]

450
00:29:18.133 --> 00:29:20.676
[Darwin] What I wouldn't
give for a cozy fire right now.

451
00:29:20.677 --> 00:29:24.139
[Alfie] Well. I had some of those heat
packs in my backpack. but they're gone.

452
00:29:24.681 --> 00:29:26.641
The gear. the food...

453
00:29:26.642 --> 00:29:28.393
[Monty] Please don't
mention food right now.

454
00:29:29.353 --> 00:29:30.479
Any idea how much longer?

455
00:29:33.148 --> 00:29:36.443
[Alfie] I guess those aliens weren't
dead after all. They were just napping.

456
00:29:37.027 --> 00:29:39.445
Yeah. but they woke up different.
like they're evolving or something.

457
00:29:39.446 --> 00:29:41.572
That's great. We barely
knew how to fight the first ones.

458
00:29:41.573 --> 00:29:43.116
How else are we
going to stop these...

459
00:29:45.202 --> 00:29:46.578
- these...
- [Darwin] Jesus.

460
00:29:50.249 --> 00:29:52.042
[Monty] Looks like
it hit those bastards.

461
00:29:52.626 --> 00:29:54.711
So this is where all
those people came from.

462
00:29:55.879 --> 00:29:57.464
[Darwin] Well.
that way's blocked.

463
00:29:58.048 --> 00:30:00.383
[Monty] Yeah. Looks like
a live wire up there as well.

464
00:30:00.384 --> 00:30:01.802
[Alfie] Let's go
through this way.

465
00:30:16.316 --> 00:30:18.076
[Alfie] It's blocked.
Let's cut through here.

466
00:30:22.823 --> 00:30:24.032
Oh. shit.

467
00:30:27.369 --> 00:30:31.330
[Darwin] It's like a car
wreck inside of a train wreck.

468
00:30:31.331 --> 00:30:32.416
What a mess.

469
00:30:33.709 --> 00:30:35.710
[Monty] Look. Penny's
exhausted and freezing.

470
00:30:35.711 --> 00:30:38.296
She needs to rest. and seeing that
we are stuck here for the moment. we...

471
00:30:38.297 --> 00:30:39.797
So you're giving up. yeah?

472
00:30:39.798 --> 00:30:42.300
- Fucking knew it.
- I'm not giving up. you prick.

473
00:30:42.301 --> 00:30:44.177
- I'm just calling a break.
- "Calling a break"?

474
00:30:44.178 --> 00:30:45.344
So you're team captain now.

475
00:30:45.345 --> 00:30:47.430
Stop fighting. both of you.

476
00:30:47.431 --> 00:30:48.682
Jam. what do you think?

477
00:30:50.642 --> 00:30:52.226
[sighs] Forget it.

478
00:30:52.227 --> 00:30:55.813
Me and Darwin will go scavenge up
some supplies to replace what we lost.

479
00:30:55.814 --> 00:30:57.774
Let's go. Enjoy
your break. yeah?

480
00:31:01.904 --> 00:31:03.238
[Monty sighs]

481
00:31:05.157 --> 00:31:06.658
[Monty] Nope. Okay.

482
00:31:07.951 --> 00:31:10.369
- Then let's check this one. yeah?
- [Penny] This one?

483
00:31:10.370 --> 00:31:11.829
- [Monty] Yes.
- [Penny] This the one?

484
00:31:11.830 --> 00:31:14.416
[sighs] Yeah.
great. This will work.

485
00:31:15.125 --> 00:31:16.627
All right. Penny. Hop in.

486
00:31:19.922 --> 00:31:22.298
See. look. Blanket
and everything.

487
00:31:22.299 --> 00:31:24.009
Okay. Penny. lie down.

488
00:31:25.511 --> 00:31:26.512
[Monty sighs]

489
00:31:27.221 --> 00:31:29.723
Okay. Pillow fort. here we come.

490
00:31:32.184 --> 00:31:35.896
[sighs] Complete with...
[sighs] ...a night-light.

491
00:31:37.439 --> 00:31:38.607
All right.

492
00:31:39.233 --> 00:31:40.317
Okay.

493
00:31:44.655 --> 00:31:45.656
Good night. Pen.

494
00:31:54.373 --> 00:31:55.916
You haven't said
a word in hours.

495
00:31:56.625 --> 00:31:57.626
Something wrong?

496
00:31:58.293 --> 00:31:59.586
Besides. I mean. everything?

497
00:32:00.712 --> 00:32:02.005
You're good with her. you know?

498
00:32:03.966 --> 00:32:05.384
You sound surprised.

499
00:32:06.051 --> 00:32:08.178
I've just never
seen you like that.

500
00:32:10.848 --> 00:32:12.558
You really know what she needs.

501
00:32:16.436 --> 00:32:20.190
What was that thing before?
"You turn left. turn right..."

502
00:32:21.400 --> 00:32:24.485
Uh... [inhales sharply] ...that.

503
00:32:24.486 --> 00:32:25.571
The maze.

504
00:32:26.655 --> 00:32:27.906
Weird. innit?

505
00:32:29.241 --> 00:32:33.036
A few years back when things got
bad at home. Penny would get these...

506
00:32:33.579 --> 00:32:34.913
These attacks. you know?

507
00:32:35.497 --> 00:32:39.041
I noticed only certain things would
calm her down like maps and...

508
00:32:39.042 --> 00:32:40.169
And bus routes.

509
00:32:40.878 --> 00:32:43.713
We'd stash them everywhere. And
when she did get scared. we'd pull one out

510
00:32:43.714 --> 00:32:45.215
and. uh. trace a path.

511
00:32:46.758 --> 00:32:51.805
But. one time we were on
a walk. and a cyclist got hit.

512
00:32:52.598 --> 00:32:56.185
Mercedes just hammered him.
The bloke flew across the street.

513
00:32:56.810 --> 00:32:57.936
a few yards from Penny.

514
00:32:58.645 --> 00:33:00.230
- Christ.
- [Monty] Yeah.

515
00:33:00.731 --> 00:33:02.065
Penny lost it.

516
00:33:02.649 --> 00:33:04.818
I mean completely
lost it. No map. nothing.

517
00:33:05.694 --> 00:33:09.823
So. on the spot. I
made up this maze.

518
00:33:10.657 --> 00:33:14.745
God. it sounds so stupid.
but... "Turn left. Turn right."

519
00:33:15.579 --> 00:33:17.499
And. uh. that's what we've
been doing ever since.

520
00:33:18.916 --> 00:33:20.292
You fixed it.

521
00:33:21.793 --> 00:33:23.128
Made it better.

522
00:33:25.088 --> 00:33:27.965
Listen. you're not to blame
for all this. You know that. right?

523
00:33:27.966 --> 00:33:29.468
But I am though.

524
00:33:30.344 --> 00:33:32.011
[exhales]

525
00:33:32.012 --> 00:33:33.555
This whole mess is on me.

526
00:33:35.057 --> 00:33:38.059
Trapped in a tunnel.
surrounded by monsters.

527
00:33:38.060 --> 00:33:41.355
Nothing to eat and no way out.

528
00:33:42.356 --> 00:33:45.192
[scoffs] And I can't fix it.

529
00:33:48.862 --> 00:33:50.280
Should've listened to my mum.

530
00:33:50.822 --> 00:33:52.823
We'd all be better off if
I'd just stayed at home.

531
00:33:52.824 --> 00:33:55.536
Not me. Not Pen.

532
00:33:56.912 --> 00:33:59.164
Nothing I said could
get her out of the house.

533
00:33:59.665 --> 00:34:00.749
I mean nothing.

534
00:34:01.875 --> 00:34:02.918
But you did.

535
00:34:03.502 --> 00:34:04.503
You gave us hope.

536
00:34:05.254 --> 00:34:06.797
And look where it got her.

537
00:34:07.923 --> 00:34:11.425
Look. it doesn't matter. okay? Penny's
not the only one who needs rest right now.

538
00:34:11.426 --> 00:34:13.052
Why don't you join
her? I'll take first watch.

539
00:34:13.053 --> 00:34:16.348
No. I don't need to
sleep. I need to think.

540
00:34:17.516 --> 00:34:18.684
Take a walk.

541
00:34:19.184 --> 00:34:21.436
- Normally helps me.
- Yeah. Got it. Thanks.

542
00:34:24.313 --> 00:34:26.649
I'm sorry. I just
wanna be alone.

543
00:34:26.650 --> 00:34:27.943
Fine. All good.

544
00:34:46.545 --> 00:34:48.213
Another couple of road flares.

545
00:34:48.714 --> 00:34:50.756
- How many does that make?
- [Darwin] Uh. five.

546
00:34:50.757 --> 00:34:54.969
Uh. plus two water bottles.
some biscuits and a tire iron.

547
00:34:55.512 --> 00:34:59.725
And some bungees and some climbing gear
from Mr. French Alps Holiday over there.

548
00:35:03.103 --> 00:35:06.147
[Alfie] No way we're going
through this. It's the end of the line.

549
00:35:06.148 --> 00:35:08.609
[Monty] You find anything
good? Pretty grim. eh?

550
00:35:09.693 --> 00:35:11.527
Yeah. Some. uh. biscuits. so...

551
00:35:11.528 --> 00:35:13.112
Oh. great. I'm starving.

552
00:35:13.113 --> 00:35:15.615
Hey! Emergencies only.

553
00:35:15.616 --> 00:35:17.617
Look around. mate.
It's the very definition.

554
00:35:17.618 --> 00:35:19.827
Alf. he's right.
The path's blocked.

555
00:35:19.828 --> 00:35:22.039
There's no getting past that.

556
00:35:22.539 --> 00:35:25.124
And plus. I'm pretty
M... Marvin anyway. so...

557
00:35:25.125 --> 00:35:27.628
Nice. Cozying up with
King Prick over here.

558
00:35:28.212 --> 00:35:31.297
When he used to torture you...
Torture Caspar back at school.

559
00:35:31.298 --> 00:35:33.591
who was it that stuck
up for you? Huh?

560
00:35:33.592 --> 00:35:34.843
- You did.
- Yeah.

561
00:35:35.427 --> 00:35:37.346
Whether I wanted you to or not.

562
00:35:39.431 --> 00:35:40.640
Excuse me?

563
00:35:40.641 --> 00:35:43.602
Look. Everything doesn't
have to be a fight. Alfie.

564
00:35:44.186 --> 00:35:47.396
We do things to survive. And yeah.
Monty was a bag of dicks back then.

565
00:35:47.397 --> 00:35:53.070
and he still can be sometimes. but
right now you're just as bad as him.

566
00:36:01.578 --> 00:36:02.829
Fine. Whatever.

567
00:36:03.622 --> 00:36:04.997
But I still don't trust you.

568
00:36:04.998 --> 00:36:09.752
- You think you know me so well. don't you?
- No. I don't at all. That's the problem.

569
00:36:09.753 --> 00:36:10.921
Fine.

570
00:36:11.880 --> 00:36:13.757
Ask me anything. Open book.

571
00:36:14.716 --> 00:36:15.801
Open book. eh?

572
00:36:17.845 --> 00:36:19.847
All right. "Kiss from a Rose."

573
00:36:20.430 --> 00:36:24.141
What's that '90s abomination
doing in your playlist?

574
00:36:24.142 --> 00:36:26.542
- Little Monty get his heart broken?
- None of your business.

575
00:36:27.896 --> 00:36:31.607
If you want trust.
this is the price.

576
00:36:31.608 --> 00:36:34.403
Open fucking book and
I just picked the page.

577
00:36:36.488 --> 00:36:38.198
[sighs. whispers] Fucking hell.

578
00:36:45.247 --> 00:36:47.708
[scoffs] It's my
parents' song. okay?

579
00:36:48.792 --> 00:36:50.042
[sighs]

580
00:36:50.043 --> 00:36:53.505
I used to watch them dance to
it when I was five or whatever.

581
00:36:54.464 --> 00:36:58.051
They used to smile at
each other. Like. real smiles.

582
00:36:58.886 --> 00:37:01.221
So. yeah. I play it sometimes

583
00:37:01.763 --> 00:37:06.310
'cause it reminds me that things...
Things were actually good once.

584
00:37:09.563 --> 00:37:10.856
Happy now. twat?

585
00:37:12.566 --> 00:37:13.609
[Monty sighs]

586
00:37:26.705 --> 00:37:27.956
[Alfie sighs]

587
00:37:44.348 --> 00:37:45.807
[sighs]

588
00:37:46.850 --> 00:37:49.686
Fine. Walk it is.

589
00:38:12.584 --> 00:38:13.585
[sighs]

590
00:38:16.380 --> 00:38:17.881
[Caspar] It's like
the bus. isn't it?

591
00:38:21.468 --> 00:38:24.096
The one Mr. Edwards was
driving before the crash.

592
00:38:25.347 --> 00:38:27.975
Looked like a
crushed-up fizzy drink can.

593
00:38:29.434 --> 00:38:30.644
We made it out alive.

594
00:38:31.478 --> 00:38:32.813
I'm dreaming again.

595
00:38:35.315 --> 00:38:36.483
Sort of.

596
00:38:37.067 --> 00:38:38.110
Yeah.

597
00:38:39.152 --> 00:38:40.696
So if I'm dreaming.

598
00:38:42.197 --> 00:38:43.657
where are you?

599
00:38:49.746 --> 00:38:50.831
I'm with them.

600
00:38:51.331 --> 00:38:52.332
Well.

601
00:38:53.375 --> 00:38:54.668
part of me is.

602
00:38:57.129 --> 00:39:02.259
Just after the hospital. with
you and that soldier. Trevante.

603
00:39:03.135 --> 00:39:04.802
I felt something pulling on me.

604
00:39:04.803 --> 00:39:06.929
It was like a... It was
like a compass needle.

605
00:39:06.930 --> 00:39:08.807
And I followed that pull.

606
00:39:10.017 --> 00:39:12.394
and it led me straight
into their world.

607
00:39:14.313 --> 00:39:15.479
Into them.

608
00:39:15.480 --> 00:39:17.065
"Into them"?

609
00:39:17.816 --> 00:39:21.904
But just know I reached out
to you with everything I had.

610
00:39:23.280 --> 00:39:25.282
And here you are. [chuckles]

611
00:39:25.991 --> 00:39:27.075
I've been looking for you.

612
00:39:29.828 --> 00:39:30.954
Me too.

613
00:39:33.165 --> 00:39:34.499
I wanted to get out.

614
00:39:35.292 --> 00:39:36.627
I... I thought I could.

615
00:39:38.629 --> 00:39:40.588
I think things got worse here.

616
00:39:40.589 --> 00:39:43.133
The radio said
something about an attack.

617
00:39:43.842 --> 00:39:46.802
Maybe it worked.
M-Maybe we hurt them.

618
00:39:46.803 --> 00:39:49.931
That's why the lights. they're flashing.
And the... And... And the sound...

619
00:39:49.932 --> 00:39:51.641
They must be right pissed.

620
00:39:51.642 --> 00:39:53.351
Whatever signal they're sending.

621
00:39:53.352 --> 00:39:55.604
I mean. they must
be stronger because...

622
00:39:57.439 --> 00:39:59.191
- I can finally see you.
- See you.

623
00:40:00.984 --> 00:40:03.194
- [Caspar chuckles] - Don't
you see what that means?

624
00:40:03.195 --> 00:40:05.197
You're still finding
ways to get back.

625
00:40:06.365 --> 00:40:10.911
Get back to me. Just like
I'm finding my way to you.

626
00:40:12.412 --> 00:40:14.248
- You are?
- Yeah.

627
00:40:15.582 --> 00:40:17.583
If you're with them. you
can learn about them.

628
00:40:17.584 --> 00:40:21.296
About what they are. how to
fight them. how to finish them.

629
00:40:21.797 --> 00:40:24.633
Then. together. we can
get you back. All of you.

630
00:40:25.759 --> 00:40:27.719
You just gotta keep trying.

631
00:40:28.262 --> 00:40:30.305
I will if you will.

632
00:40:35.060 --> 00:40:36.478
I'm not giving up.

633
00:40:38.230 --> 00:40:39.231
Ever.

634
00:40:45.612 --> 00:40:47.781
[whispering] Hey. Monty. Monty.

635
00:40:48.448 --> 00:40:50.658
- What is it?
- You have a good sense of direction. yeah?

636
00:40:50.659 --> 00:40:51.743
"Turn left. turn right"?

637
00:40:52.327 --> 00:40:53.911
Yeah. Uh. yeah.

638
00:40:53.912 --> 00:40:55.371
Time to fix this.

639
00:40:55.372 --> 00:40:57.875
[aliens roaring. howling]

640
00:41:37.789 --> 00:41:39.291
[aliens growling]

641
00:41:45.422 --> 00:41:46.798
[Penny] Monty!

642
00:41:49.259 --> 00:41:51.260
Monty. where are you?

643
00:41:51.261 --> 00:41:53.971
Alfie! Alfie! Alfie!

644
00:41:53.972 --> 00:41:57.100
- What? What happened?
- They're coming. I heard them.

645
00:41:59.478 --> 00:42:01.145
[groans] Someone's
gone through my things.

646
00:42:01.146 --> 00:42:02.689
I knew it. What did he take?

647
00:42:03.190 --> 00:42:04.440
- Climbing gear.
- What?

648
00:42:04.441 --> 00:42:06.318
[Jamila] You're up. Good.

649
00:42:07.236 --> 00:42:08.236
'Cause we're leaving.

650
00:42:08.237 --> 00:42:09.863
Come on. guys.

651
00:42:12.491 --> 00:42:17.578
See? It's a path through all this mess.
Just follow the rope and mind the glass.

652
00:42:17.579 --> 00:42:19.247
He had to break some windows.

653
00:42:19.248 --> 00:42:20.332
Monty!

654
00:42:21.667 --> 00:42:22.834
You did this?

655
00:42:22.835 --> 00:42:24.002
Yeah. I did.

656
00:42:24.795 --> 00:42:26.212
Ready?

657
00:42:26.213 --> 00:42:27.505
Great. [grunts]

658
00:42:27.506 --> 00:42:28.674
Follow me. Pen.

659
00:42:34.972 --> 00:42:37.099
[bellowing]

660
00:42:54.032 --> 00:42:57.703
[banging. growling]

661
00:43:21.351 --> 00:43:23.144
- [Jamila] Any cuts? Mmm?
- I don't think so.

662
00:43:23.145 --> 00:43:24.897
- [Jamila] All good? Okay.
- Mm-hmm.

663
00:43:25.480 --> 00:43:26.565
[Monty sighs]

664
00:43:27.232 --> 00:43:28.817
[aliens growling]

665
00:43:29.401 --> 00:43:32.487
- They're coming. Let's go! Come on.
- [Monty] Go. go. go.

666
00:43:33.113 --> 00:43:34.865
[roaring]

667
00:43:41.914 --> 00:43:44.123
[Darwin] Did you notice
we're running uphill?

668
00:43:44.124 --> 00:43:45.834
We must be near the end.

669
00:43:46.627 --> 00:43:47.628
Look!

670
00:43:50.339 --> 00:43:51.840
- Oh. no.
- [Alfie] What the hell?

671
00:43:53.550 --> 00:43:55.710
- [Monty] Guys. please... -
[Darwin] Look at the walls.

672
00:43:55.886 --> 00:43:56.970
What?

673
00:44:00.307 --> 00:44:01.183
[Monty] Jesus.

674
00:44:01.184 --> 00:44:03.893
Those are explosives. They're
gonna blow the entrance to the tunnel.

675
00:44:03.894 --> 00:44:05.520
- [Jamila] Oh. God.
- [Monty] Fuck. Help!

676
00:44:05.521 --> 00:44:07.272
[all shouting] Help!

677
00:44:08.440 --> 00:44:10.483
Anyone! Please! Help! Please!

678
00:44:10.484 --> 00:44:11.902
Please! Please! Help!

679
00:44:12.778 --> 00:44:13.779
[Jamila] Anyone!

680
00:44:14.780 --> 00:44:16.907
[shouting continues]

681
00:44:19.535 --> 00:44:21.578
[shouting continues]

682
00:44:24.915 --> 00:44:25.832
[in French] Hey!

683
00:44:25.833 --> 00:44:29.585
Someone's in the tunnel!
Hey! Someone's in there!

684
00:44:29.586 --> 00:44:31.003
What are you talking about?

685
00:44:31.004 --> 00:44:32.164
It sounds like children. sir.

686
00:44:32.381 --> 00:44:34.591
I need six men. now!

687
00:44:35.425 --> 00:44:37.094
[clamoring]

688
00:44:40.180 --> 00:44:42.224
[growling]

689
00:44:44.476 --> 00:44:46.644
[Jamila. in English] Oh. my
God. There's someone there.

690
00:44:46.645 --> 00:44:48.479
- [soldier 1] Come on.
- [Jamila] Hurry. hurry. hurry!

691
00:44:48.480 --> 00:44:49.772
Climb up! Climb up!

692
00:44:49.773 --> 00:44:51.065
[Monty] Climb up! Get her up!

693
00:44:51.066 --> 00:44:53.234
- [Jamila] Hurry. hurry. hurry!
- [Monty] Pen. go.

694
00:44:53.235 --> 00:44:54.355
[Jamila] Go. go. go. go. go!

695
00:44:57.155 --> 00:44:59.575
[bellowing]

696
00:45:02.119 --> 00:45:04.036
- [Penny] Monty!
- [in French] Clear the barricade!

697
00:45:04.037 --> 00:45:05.454
[in English] Hurry! Hurry!

698
00:45:05.455 --> 00:45:07.665
- [Jamila] Go. go. go. go!
- [Monty] Come on. I got you.

699
00:45:07.666 --> 00:45:08.906
[Jamila] Quick. they're coming!

700
00:45:11.378 --> 00:45:12.628
[in French] Ready the charges!

701
00:45:12.629 --> 00:45:13.881
- [in English] Darwin!
- Monty!

702
00:45:18.802 --> 00:45:20.304
- [Darwin shouts]
- [thud]

703
00:45:20.721 --> 00:45:21.721
[in French] On my signal!

704
00:45:23.974 --> 00:45:26.727
Three... two... one!

705
00:45:42.284 --> 00:45:43.952
[soldiers murmuring]

706
00:46:00.844 --> 00:46:04.723
- All clear!
- [soldiers shout. cheer]

707
00:46:05.891 --> 00:46:06.975
[Jamila sighs]

708
00:46:08.268 --> 00:46:12.230
[stammering. in
English] Thanks. mate.

709
00:46:12.231 --> 00:46:13.856
- Yeah. welcome.
- [Darwin] Fuck.

710
00:46:13.857 --> 00:46:15.483
- [Penny] Monty!
- Pen.

711
00:46:15.484 --> 00:46:18.487
- Hey. I thought you was dead in there.
- Yeah. I did too.

712
00:46:19.363 --> 00:46:21.281
- You all right?
- [Darwin exclaims] Fuck!

713
00:46:22.991 --> 00:46:26.452
- [groans] Nicked me. God.
[groaning] - [Alfie] Fucking hell.

714
00:46:26.453 --> 00:46:27.538
Darwin.

715
00:46:28.205 --> 00:46:30.581
- [Alfie] Someone's coming.
- [Jamila] Medic. Medic!

716
00:46:30.582 --> 00:46:32.124
[Alfie] Come on. Pick him up.

717
00:46:32.125 --> 00:46:33.376
[Monty] Go.

718
00:46:33.377 --> 00:46:34.836
[Darwin groans. pants]

719
00:46:34.837 --> 00:46:37.129
[Alfie] Come on. You're
gonna be fine. okay?

720
00:46:37.130 --> 00:46:39.340
Look. there's medics here.
They're gonna get you good.

721
00:46:39.341 --> 00:46:41.009
[Monty] This lot's
gonna fix you right up.

722
